Welcome to the LPmud 2.4.5 mudlib!

To log in, enter the name of your game character at the prompt. If this
is your first time, a new character will be created and you will be asked
for a password and a couple of other things.

Once logged in, type 'help' to see a list of available commands. You move
by giving directions (e.g. 'north', 'south', 'east', 'west', 'up', 'down',
or their abbreviations 'n', 's', 'e', 'w', 'u', 'd'). Diagonal movement
is also supported ('ne', 'nw', 'se', 'sw').

Other useful commands:
  look            - examine your surroundings
  inventory (i)   - see what you are carrying
  get / drop      - pick up or drop items
  say <message>   - speak to others in the room
  kill <monster>  - attack a monster
  score           - view your stats and experience

Explore the world, defeat monsters, and gain experience. When you reach
level 20, you will be promoted to wizard!

Enjoy your adventure!

